Disappointed. Don't let the nice cover art fool you, this documentary about Messi was poorly produced/edited. The best I can tell is that this is a "60 minutes" program spliced into another program. At times, the film poorly transitions between these two, even cutting off the narrator mid-sentence to jump to the other program. The overall feel is disjointed and lacks the compelling background music you might be familiar with in most sports documentaries.

I won't criticize the storytellers for Messi's guarded nature, he is truly a man of few words and doesn't enjoy media exposure or interviews. His personality is refreshing in a world full of ego-fueled football stars. But honestly, I should have spent my money on a highlight video because I'm not going to watch this again.
